ingredients:
Â½ Lt of milk cream
Sweet cookie of your choice
250 grams of dulce de leche
100 Gr of butter at room temperature
Meringue to accompany (You can learn to make meringue here)
Preparation:
In a bowl, beat the milk cream with half of the dulce de leche until the mixture takes consistency.
Crush the biscuits and mix them with the butter until obtaining a coarse biscuit sand.
In layers we are going to place the preparation of the cookies in a glass or glass, then we incorporate the mixture of dulce de leche and milk cream, then a layer of dulce de leche and finally we add crushed pieces of meringue.
We put in the fridge for 30 minutes.
Once cold the dessert can be tasted.
